  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I returned from the forest, I returned-- I-- I-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When I was in the forest, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Germans had sent in a sonderkommando, with their faithful allies the Ukrainians.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Ukrainians were murder assistants that were highly proficient.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They simply were outstanding killers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The description I got then and, again, when I visited the same place, the-- the-- the little-- the little marketplace in Gorlice, again, two years ago, I spoke to the Polish who lived around it.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was the same description I got.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Those people, who were aged, sick, diseased, crippled, they were simply grabbed by arms and legs and thrown on hay wagons, one on top of another, and beaten with rifle butts.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The blood was draining all over.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Those on the bottom were suffocating.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were simply dragged out by horse-- by horse-drawn hay wagons to the-- to where the Jewish cemetery was and buried alive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "According to-- now this is not eyewitness.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This is according to the description of the Polish people who lived around [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the-- the place of-- where the Jews were rounded up in Gorlice.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And also, the lady, the Polish lady, who verified it, who is-- who lives within the Jewish cemetery, today, and did at that time, too.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] This-- this story, had been-- we had-- we were told similar stories occurring in other places.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We could not believe it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But, apparently, the Germans had developed a pattern on how to go about it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the same thing came to our ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I returned, they had already done away with all the Jews that they thought are useless.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
